The paper discusses topic modeling and network models of topics in the International Conference on Computational Science corpus, which contains domain-specific (computational science) papers over sixteen years. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-categories of computer science that deal with data analysis, machine learning, and natural language processing, such as cs.DL (Digital Libraries), cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CL (Computation and Language).
